# Testing Governance

- Treat automated tests as the source of truth. If relevant tests do not exist or do not pass, the work is not complete.
- Every new service, server action, or business-logic module must ship with a corresponding `.test.ts` file.
- Use Vitest for business logic and integration coverage such as lead scoring, prompt construction, tenant config transforms, and billing calculations.
- Use Playwright for critical flows such as tenant onboarding, outbound dispatch, iframe widget loading, and multi-tenant subdomain routing.
- Never make real third-party API calls in unit tests. Mock Resend, Cal.com, OpenAI, and similar boundaries.
- When editing code that already has automated coverage, use the `regression-sentinel` skill and get back to green before moving on.
- When UI or routing changes affect tenant resolution, add or update a Playwright assertion that proves the rewrite or subdomain behavior works.
- Do not report work as complete until the relevant tests pass and the required runtime and compile-time verification has been performed.
